         <abstract>
            <p>In this paper we give criteria for a complex number to be an approximate zero of a polynomial $f$ for Newton's method or for the $k$th-order Euler method. An approximate zero for the $k$th-order Euler method is an initial point from which the method converges with an order $(k + 1)$. Also, we construct families of Newton (and Euler) type algorithms which are surely convergent.</p>
          </abstract>
